## Summary of Changes and Why

| Change | Reason |
|---|---|
| `readLE<T>` / `writeLE<T>` with `bswap` + `memcpy` | Eliminates byte-by-byte LSB loops; PowerPC has `lwbrx`/`stwbrx` which GCC emits for this pattern |
| `__builtin_memcpy` in `readLE`/`writeLE` | Avoids UB from type-punning; GCC lowers to single `lwz`/`stw` + `bswap` |
| `LIKELY`/`UNLIKELY` on hot-path null checks | Broadway's branch predictor is static; hints dramatically help |
| `getVramMapping9` helper | Deduplicates the 5-way switch, helps icache |
| `const` on read methods | Enables optimizer to elide reloads through `core` pointer |
| `BIT(7)` → `0x80` in `updateVram` | Avoids macro expansion overhead; constant folded anyway but cleaner |
| Cached `dsiMode`/`gbaMode` locals in `updateMap` loops | Prevents repeated pointer chasing through `core` each iteration |
| `__builtin_memset` in constructor | Guaranteed single call; won't be optimized away |
| Separate `VramMapping` template specializations | Avoids inner byte loop; single `lwbrx`-class instruction per mapping |
